  <Summary>The Monster in Clay!: The sculptor Dwight Courtney models a bust of a black sorcerer from the past. He seems to gain uncanny abilities: whatever he makes is destroyed in real life. After the death of three of his colleagues, Courtney investigates the strange accidents.

The Telltale Hand!: George Karyl kills his client John Putnam and hides the body but the lines on his palm begin to form a hangman's noose.

Mysterious Princess!: Account of a vagrant who called herself "Caraboo."

The Hidden Author!: An Ouija board dictates poetry.

I Was a Ghost for Hire!: A medium and her aide stage elaborate seances and incorporate the dead very convincingly. The racket is brought down by frightening the ghost impersonators with a ghost impersonation.

The Devil Was My Partner!: Arthur Drake gets addicted to casino gambling in Naples, Italy. He signs a pact with the devil and now wins every time he gambles. Satan, however, is an impostor and casino owner who steals Drake's identity to continue his life in the US.

</Summary>
